HEADWORD: Zendik
<hw>Zen"dik</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>zand⟦imac⟧k</ets>.]</ety> <def>An atheist or unbeliever; -- name
given in the East to those charged with disbelief of any revealed
religion, or accused of magical heresies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zenick</ent>⟦br⟧
